{
  "texts": [
    "The research did not provide a new classification method but suggested a set of features to provide an accurate Arabic classifier.",
    "The researchers built a lexical wordlist and an Arabic natural language processing (ANLP) architectural tool to extract the textual features, including POS, emotion, polarity, and syntactic.",
    "Based on these features, RF, SVM, and NB were used and tested for each single feature and a combination of features.",
    "The best result was registered for RF, with a combination of POS, syntactic and semantic roles, and contextual polarity features, which achieved an F1-score of 79%.",
    "Moreover, the research tested against human performance, providing 86% of articles classified correctly."
  ]
}